@startuml
title Device Monitoring System - Metric Processing Flow

actor "Device\n(Router / Server)" as Device
participant "API Service\n(Ingestion)" as API
queue "Kafka Topic\n(device.metrics.raw)" as Kafka
participant "Worker Service\n(Consumer)" as Consumer
database "MongoDB\n(metrics)" as Mongo
participant "Alert Service\n(Telegram)" as Alert

== 1. Data Ingestion ==
Device -> API: POST /api/v1/metrics\n(JSON: device_id, metric, value, timestamp)
activate API

API -> API: Extract payload & Validate input
API -> API: generate_uuid() & utc_now_iso()
API -> API: build_event() \n(Format as Nested JSON Event Object)
API -> Kafka: Publish event
activate Kafka
Kafka --> API: Produce ACK
deactivate Kafka

API --> Device: HTTP 200 OK\n(Returns event_id & status)
deactivate API

== 2. Asynchronous Processing ==
Kafka -> Consumer: Dispatch Event / Consume payload
activate Consumer

Consumer -> Consumer: Extract payload\n(Parse device_id, metric, value)
Consumer -> Consumer: Evaluate thresholds\n(NORMAL, WARNING, CRITICAL)

== 3. Data Persistence ==
Consumer -> Consumer: MetricDocument.build_document()\n(Merge event with evaluated status)
Consumer -> Mongo: MetricDocument.insert_one()
activate Mongo
Mongo -> Mongo: Inject created_time & updated_time
Mongo --> Consumer: Return inserted_id
deactivate Mongo

== 4. Alert Triggering ==
alt status == "CRITICAL"
    Consumer -> Alert: get_alert_service().send_alert()
    activate Alert
    Alert -> Alert: Format Telegram message
    Alert --> Consumer: Alert Dispatched
    deactivate Alert
else status == "NORMAL" or "WARNING"
    Consumer -> Consumer: Skip Alert
end

deactivate Consumer
@enduml